Shudufhadzo Musida has been crowned Miss South Africa 2020. JOHANNESBURG - Newly-crowned Miss SA, Shudufhadzo Musida says mental health needs to be destigmatised. Musida arrived at the OR Tambo International Airport on Sunday, where she was welcomed by Sports, Arts and Culture Minister, Nathi Mthethwa. READ: Shudufhadzo Musida's home village jubilant after Miss SA win Speaking at the airport Musida says mental health is an important topic especially because of COVID-19. "People have lost their jobs and a lot of people have lost loved ones," she said. "Now is the time to start the conversation to engage with it."